choices.text:
why does this command give error Permission denied (publickey):

ssh -i \“~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
The error "Permission denied (publickey)" indicates that the private key file specified in the command does not have permission to access the remote server. This could be due to incorrect permissions on the private key file or an issue with the SSH configuration for the remote server. To resolve this, try running the command again using sudo or changing the permissions of the private key file to allow it to read and write files.
